                <head>No. 36.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lothrop</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-02-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 22, 1888</date>. (Received March
                        12.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 161.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 110, relative to the
                    protection of fur-bearing seals in the Behring Sea, has just reached me, and I
                    have lost no time in making known to the imperial Government your wishes
                    respecting the co-operation of the Russian ambassador in London with Mr. Phelps
                    on this subject.</p>
                <p>Very truly, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. V. N. Lothrop.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
